vehicles.name: Toyota Yaris
vehicles.description: Exploring the city in style or run some errands with the Toyota Yaris. Fuel efficient, with air conditioning and plenty of space for four people, you'll get your bearings in no time using one of these zippy runabouts.

vehicles.name: Mazda Demio
vehicles.description: Also known as a Mazda 2, its easy access and a high seating position make a car that is extremely popular especially with our older clients that require vehicles easy to get in and out of. They will seat 5 passengers and the generous luggage area can take 3 large cases.

vehicles.name: Toyota Corolla Hatch
vehicles.description: The Toyota Corolla Hatch isn’t just sporty, economical and great on the road but it's also New Zealand top selling car and for a good reason.The 5 star ANCAP rated Corolla Hatch gives you peace of mind wherever your travels take you.

vehicles.name: Ford Focus Trend
vehicles.description: Sporting a sleek new exterior design, new alloy wheels, and a modern interior with intuitive controls. Feel at ease knowing the new Ford Focus makes safety a top priority. That's why it includes six airbags, standard Anti-Lock Braking System (ABS), Electronic Stability Program and an ultra-high-strength safety cage.

vehicles.name: Toyota Corolla
vehicles.description: Rent a compact car that's a perennial favorite. When you rent a Toyota Corolla, you're not only getting seating for five and plenty of room for all your gear – you're getting technology, innovation, comfort and safety features that really are among some of the best.

vehicles.name: Toyota Camry
vehicles.description: A Toyota Camry rental car is a staple in the industry and a popular choice for those who want a little extra passenger space without sacrificing too much in terms of fuel economy. The Camry seats up to 5 adults comfortably, making road trips across country a breeze.

vehicles.name: Holden Commodore
vehicles.description: The Holden Commodore reimagines luxury without compromising on performance. The Commodore is one of the most advanced vehicles to wear the Holden badge, thanks to the wide array of cutting-edge technology features integrated throughout the vehicle.

vehicles.name: Toyota Highlander
vehicles.description: Seize your adventure and take the family with you. With 7-seats, 2 tonne towing capacity and Toyota Safety Sense, this all-round recreational SUV has the functional features you need.

vehicles.name: Toyota Rav4 2WD
vehicles.description: With a Toyota RAV4 you are getting a vehicle that offers a winning combination of safety, economy, comfort and performance. The Rav4 includes stability control, anti-lock brakes, brake assist, traction control, and ten  airbags.

vehicles.name: Hyundai iMax
vehicles.description: Big, strong, and reliable, the iMax is hugely practical and extremely cost efficient. Dual front and side airbags, ABS brakes and Electronic Stability Control (ESC) come as standard. The iMax can comfortably carry up to 8 passengers making it perfect for larger groups.

vehicles.name: Audi RS5 Convertable
vehicles.description: The stunning Audi RS5 cabriolet is a four-seater convertible blending premium exterior and interior looks with incredible performance and all-wheel-drive versatility. The drop-top RS5 is powered by a glorious hand-built 4.2-litre V8 and produces 444bhp and 317lb ft. The Audi RS5 is sure to impress car lovers with the style, power and practicality compared with many other luxury sports cars.

vehicles.name: Maserati Quattroporte Sport GT
vehicles.description: With one of the sexiest exhaust notes this side of an F430, balanced and fluent handling, and a relatively supple ride, the Quattroporte is the well-heeled enthusiast’s luxury sedan. Spacious, refined Italian leather interior, the Quattroporte is a ultimate in Italian style with a four door saloon car wrapped around the 400hp Ferrari V8 that it’s famous for.
